<tr id="L11"><td><a href="#L11">11</a></td><td>CHEKOV:  Aye, sir. Thirty eight thousand and closing.</td></tr>

<tr id="L12"><td><a href="#L12">12</a></td><td>KIRK:  Well, Scotty?</td></tr>

<tr id="L13"><td><a href="#L13">13</a></td><td>SCOTT:  It beats me, but isn't she a beauty?</td></tr>

<tr id="L14"><td><a href="#L14">14</a></td><td>KIRK:  Interesting design.</td></tr>

<tr id="L15"><td><a href="#L15">15</a></td><td>SCOTT:  I've never seen anything like her. And ion propulsion at that. They could teach us a thing or two.</td></tr>

<tr id="L16"><td><a href="#L16">16</a></td><td>KIRK:  Life forms, Mister Spock?</td></tr>

<tr id="L17"><td><a href="#L17">17</a></td><td>SPOCK:  One. Humanoid or similar. Low level of activity. Life-support systems functioning. Interior atmosphere, conventional nitrogen-oxygen. Instruments indicate a transferal beam emanating from the area of the humanoid life form.</td></tr>

<tr id="L18"><td><a href="#L18">18</a></td><td>KIRK:  Directed at what?</td></tr>

<tr id="L19"><td><a href="#L19">19</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Directed at the Bridge of the Enterprise, Captain.</td></tr>

