<tr id="L47"><td><a href="#L47">47</a></td><td>MCCOY:  I don't know.</td></tr>

<tr id="L48"><td><a href="#L48">48</a></td><td>KIRK:  You've got him on complete life support. Was he dead?</td></tr>

<tr id="L49"><td><a href="#L49">49</a></td><td>MCCOY:  He was worse than dead.</td></tr>

<tr id="L50"><td><a href="#L50">50</a></td><td>KIRK:  What do you mean?</td></tr>

<tr id="L51"><td><a href="#L51">51</a></td><td>MCCOY:  Jim.</td></tr>

<tr id="L52"><td><a href="#L52">52</a></td><td>KIRK:  Come on, Bones. What's the mystery?</td></tr>

<tr id="L53"><td><a href="#L53">53</a></td><td>MCCOY:  His brain is gone.</td></tr>

<tr id="L54"><td><a href="#L54">54</a></td><td>KIRK:  His what?</td></tr>

<tr id="L55"><td><a href="#L55">55</a></td><td>MCCOY:  It's been removed surgically.</td></tr>

<tr id="L56"><td><a href="#L56">56</a></td><td>KIRK:  How could he survive?</td></tr>

<tr id="L57"><td><a href="#L57">57</a></td><td>MCCOY:  It's the greatest technical job I've ever seen. Every nerve ending in the brain must've been neatly sealed. Nothing ripped, nothing torn, no bleeding. It's a medical miracle.</td></tr>

<tr id="L58"><td><a href="#L58">58</a></td><td>KIRK:  If his brain is missing, then Spock is dying.</td></tr>

<tr id="L59"><td><a href="#L59">59</a></td><td>MCCOY:  No. That incredible Vulcan physique hung on until the life-support cycle took over. His body lives. The autonomic functions continue. But there is no mind.</td></tr>

<tr id="L60"><td><a href="#L60">60</a></td><td>KIRK:  That girl.</td></tr>

<tr id="L61"><td><a href="#L61">61</a></td><td>SCOTT:  Aye.</td></tr>

<tr id="L62"><td><a href="#L62">62</a></td><td>MCCOY:  What girl?</td></tr>

<tr id="L63"><td><a href="#L63">63</a></td><td>KIRK:  From that ship. She took it. I don't know why, or where, but she must have taken it. Bones, how long can you keep him functioning?</td></tr>

<tr id="L64"><td><a href="#L64">64</a></td><td>MCCOY:  I can't give you any guarantee.</td></tr>

<tr id="L65"><td><a href="#L65">65</a></td><td>KIRK:  That's not good enough, Doctor.</td></tr>

<tr id="L66"><td><a href="#L66">66</a></td><td>MCCOY:  If it happened to any of us, I'd say indefinitely. But Vulcan physiology limits what I can do. Spock's body is more dependent on that tremendous brain for life support.</td></tr>

<tr id="L67"><td><a href="#L67">67</a></td><td>KIRK:  Then we'll take him with us.</td></tr>

<tr id="L68"><td><a href="#L68">68</a></td><td>MCCOY:  Take him? Take him where?</td></tr>

<tr id="L69"><td><a href="#L69">69</a></td><td>KIRK:  In search of his brain, Doctor. From what you say, the moment we find it we must restore it to his body, or we lose him.</td></tr>

<tr id="L70"><td><a href="#L70">70</a></td><td>MCCOY:  Jim, where are you going to look? In this whole galaxy, where are you going to look for Spock's brain? How are you going to find it?</td></tr>

<tr id="L71"><td><a href="#L71">71</a></td><td>KIRK:  I'll find it.</td></tr>

<tr id="L72"><td><a href="#L72">72</a></td><td>MCCOY:  Even if you do, I can't restore it. I don't have the medical technique.</td></tr>

<tr id="L73"><td><a href="#L73">73</a></td><td>KIRK:  It was taken out. It can be put back in.</td></tr>

<tr id="L74"><td><a href="#L74">74</a></td><td>MCCOY:  But I don't know how.</td></tr>

<tr id="L75"><td><a href="#L75">75</a></td><td>KIRK:  The thief that took it has the knowledge. I'll force it out of her.</td></tr>

<tr id="L76"><td><a href="#L76">76</a></td><td>MCCOY:  If you don't find it in twenty four hours, you'd better forget the whole thing, Jim.</td></tr>

<tr id="L77"><td><a href="#L77">77</a></td><td>KIRK:  You and Scotty have Spock ready.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Bridge</td></tr>
